main event: A report of multiple unidentified objects was submitted on October 2, 1966, noting sightings in Kansas City.
interesting points: The report indicates a sighting of approximately 100 objects hovering,The objects were described as having an oval shape with a flat bottom, resembling parachutes,The observation lasted about 5 minutes before the objects began to ascend,The objects were observed during a football game where colored balloons were also released, suggesting a possible explanation,Multiple witnesses from a household corroborated the sighting.
witness description: A girl and her household members, including her mother and other neighbors
